WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.450 --> 00:00:03.870
- There are lots of ways
AI can help you at work.

2
00:00:03.870 --> 00:00:06.150
Sure, it can help you
come up with a catchy name

3
00:00:06.150 --> 00:00:07.440
for your next product,

4
00:00:07.440 --> 00:00:09.390
but to get the most out of AI,

5
00:00:09.390 --> 00:00:11.820
it takes a bit of a mindset shift.

6
00:00:11.820 --> 00:00:13.240
What do I mean?

7
00:00:13.240 --> 00:00:16.200
Well, imagine the following scenario.

8
00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:18.150
You're faced with a high stakes goal

9
00:00:18.150 --> 00:00:19.890
of growing your business unit's revenue

10
00:00:19.890 --> 00:00:21.780
by the end of the year.

11
00:00:21.780 --> 00:00:24.270
Instead of just using AI to
draft a note to your team

12
00:00:24.270 --> 00:00:25.830
announcing your project,

13
00:00:25.830 --> 00:00:28.620
try using AI as a collaborator.

14
00:00:28.620 --> 00:00:30.330
Ask it to help you build your forecast

15
00:00:30.330 --> 00:00:33.060
and generate options for increasing sales.

16
00:00:33.060 --> 00:00:35.130
Have it help you pressure-test assumptions

17
00:00:35.130 --> 00:00:36.570
and identify risks.

18
00:00:36.570 --> 00:00:39.090
Then explore different revenue scenarios.

19
00:00:39.090 --> 00:00:40.320
See the difference?

20
00:00:40.320 --> 00:00:43.530
The real benefit isn't just
in solving one-off tasks.

21
00:00:43.530 --> 00:00:46.110
It's in collaborating to
help you solve a problem,

22
00:00:46.110 --> 00:00:48.270
navigating across various steps,

23
00:00:48.270 --> 00:00:49.710
and enlisting its help

24
00:00:49.710 --> 00:00:51.887
to set you up for making better decisions.

25
00:00:51.887 --> 00:00:54.330
But to really get the most out of AI,

26
00:00:54.330 --> 00:00:57.210
you'll have to use your
unique expertise and judgment

27
00:00:57.210 --> 00:00:59.477
to guide your collaboration with it.

28
00:00:59.477 --> 00:01:02.340
Your role is essential.

29
00:01:02.340 --> 00:01:05.520
You're the one with context
and emotional intelligence.

30
00:01:05.520 --> 00:01:08.280
Yes, AI can help you
create a presentation,

31
00:01:08.280 --> 00:01:10.980
but only you know your audience.

32
00:01:10.980 --> 00:01:13.920
AI can offer solutions to
a customer service problem,

33
00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:15.690
but only you can be the final judge

34
00:01:15.690 --> 00:01:18.720
if those solutions should be
presented to the customer.

35
00:01:18.720 --> 00:01:22.140
And there are times when AI
might not be right for the job.

36
00:01:22.140 --> 00:01:23.790
It has limitations.

37
00:01:23.790 --> 00:01:26.940
For example, topics like financial, legal,

38
00:01:26.940 --> 00:01:28.140
and compliance advice

39
00:01:28.140 --> 00:01:30.990
may be too sensitive or risky for AI.

40
00:01:30.990 --> 00:01:34.020
Connect with a professional
on these sensitive topics.

41
00:01:34.020 --> 00:01:37.530
But in cases when AI is
the right fit for the task,

42
00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:40.080
you should know how to
get the most out of it.

43
00:01:40.080 --> 00:01:42.420
The idea is not to add to your to-do list,

44
00:01:42.420 --> 00:01:45.450
but to help with the
things you're already doing

45
00:01:45.450 --> 00:01:47.940
and to help you do new things

46
00:01:47.940 --> 00:01:50.463
that previously may
not have been possible.